-- McGraw-Hill second quarter earnings fall 23 pct
-- 
-- Tue Jul 29, 2008 7:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/29/us-mcgrawhill-results-idUSWNAB315220080729

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - McGraw-Hill Cos MHP.N, a textbook publisher and bond rating company, said on Tuesday that second quarter earnings dropped 23 percent, as revenue at its bond rating business declined. 

 Second quarter earnings were $212.3 million, or 66 cents a share, compared with $277.1 million, or 79 cents, in the same period last year. (Reporting by  Dan Wilchins )